column2: I generally consider changes to be a negative thing.
column3: I’ll take a routine day over a day full of unexpected events any time.
column4: I like to do the same old things rather than try new and different ones.
column5: Whenever my life forms a stable routine, I look for ways to change it.
column6: I’d rather be bored than surprised.
column7: If I were to be informed that there’s going to be a significant change regarding the way things are done at work, I would probably feel stressed
column8: When I am informed of a change of plans, I tense up a bit.
column9: When things don’t go according to plans, it stresses me out.
column10: If my boss changed the criteria for evaluating employees, it would probably make me feel uncomfortable even if I thought I’d do just as well without having to do any extra work.
column11: Changing plans seems like a real hassle to me.
column12: Often, I feel a bit uncomfortable even about changes that may potentially improve my life
column13: When someone pressures me to change something, I tend to resist it even if I think the change may ultimately benefit me.
column14: I sometimes find myself avoiding changes that I know will be good for me
column16: I don’t change my mind easily.
column17: Once I have come to a conclusion, I’m not likely to change my mind.
column18: My views are very consistent over time.
